---
// The dispatch (CHK-4.2) — the notify-me page for Somnary's future newsletter. The SHELL is
// server-rendered and crawlable: what the dispatch will be, when it starts (not yet), and the
// reader-funded / no-brand-money stance. Only the email capture is an enhanced form island
// (<NewsletterForm/>), which degrades to a plain POST with JS off.
//
// HONESTY (real-promises rule, D2): the newsletter does NOT publish yet. Nothing here promises a
// cadence, a subscriber count, or content you'll receive now. It collects an email so we can send
// ONE note when it launches. No brand money, no sponsorship — consistent with /privacy.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import ContextBanner from '../components/ContextBanner.astro';
import Disclaimer from '../components/Disclaimer.astro';
import NewsletterForm from '../components/NewsletterForm.astro';
---

<Base
  title="The dispatch — evidence updates & the correction log — Somnary"
  description="The dispatch is Somnary's future email: evidence updates and the public correction log, when a remedy's grade or evidence changes. It isn't publishing yet — leave your email and we'll tell you once, when it launches. Reader-funded, no brand money, no spam."
  canonical="https://somnary.vercel.app/dispatch"
>
  <main class="page">
    <header class="head">
      <p class="eyebrow">The dispatch</p>
      <h1 class="title">The dispatch</h1>
      <p class="dek">
        An occasional email about what changed in the evidence: when a remedy’s grade moves, when a
        new trial shifts the picture, and what landed in the public correction log. It isn’t
        publishing yet — leave your email and we’ll tell you once, when it launches.
      </p>
    </header>

    <ContextBanner
      note="The dispatch isn’t live yet. This page collects an email so we can notify you when it starts — it doesn’t sign you up for anything today."
    />

    <div class="form-slot">
      <NewsletterForm />
    </div>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="what-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">What it will be</p>
      <h2 id="what-heading" class="section-title">What the dispatch will carry</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Somnary grades published human evidence for natural sleep remedies, and that evidence
          moves. The dispatch is how we’ll tell you when it does — plainly, without hype.
        </p>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li><strong>Evidence updates:</strong> when a new trial or review changes what a grade rests on.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>The correction log:</strong> what we got wrong and fixed, drawn from the public
            <a href="/changelog">evidence change-log</a>.
          </li>
          <li><strong>New pages:</strong> when a remedy or context page is published or substantially revised.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          What it will <strong>not</strong> be: no product picks, no “take this tonight”, no doses
          for you, no sponsored anything. It describes evidence — it never tells you what to take.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="funding-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">How it’s funded</p>
      <h2 id="funding-heading" class="section-title">Reader-funded, no brand money</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Somnary takes zero affiliate links and zero brand money — that’s core to what it is. The
          dispatch is part of the same promise: your email is used only to send you the dispatch,
          it’s never sold or shared, and every issue will carry a one-click unsubscribe. You can
          ask us to remove you any time at
          <a href="mailto:sammymoz@gmail.com">sammymoz@gmail.com</a>. How we handle your data is in
          the <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="disclaimer-slot">
      <Disclaimer variant="standard" />
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--sp-8) var(--sp-7) var(--sp-9);
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-label);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .head {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);
  }
  .title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    line-height: var(--lh-3xl);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: var(--sp-3) 0 var(--sp-5);
  }
  .dek {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--lh-md);
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 68ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .form-slot {
    margin: var(--sp-6) 0 var(--sp-8);
  }

  .section {
    border-top: var(--border-hairline);
    padding-top: var(--sp-6);
    margin-top: var(--sp-8);
  }
  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: var(--lh-xl);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: var(--sp-2) 0 var(--sp-5);
  }
  .prose {
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  .prose p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--lh-base);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-4);
  }
  .prose strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }
  .bullets {
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-4);
    padding-left: var(--sp-5);
  }
  .bullets li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--lh-base);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-2);
  }
  .bullets strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .bullets a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .disclaimer-slot {
    margin-top: var(--sp-8);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page {
      padding: var(--sp-6) var(--sp-5) var(--sp-8);
    }
    .title {
      font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    }
  }
</style>
